#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Atlas's pre-delivery quality gate. Three passes — gen, Critique, Fix — before any visual direction, mood board, or prompt architecture is delivered. Stark never sees the process, only the
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|A weak visual brief sent to Pixel creates a failed batch. A batch QC failure rate above 20% means the prompt architecture failed — not Pixel. This protocol catches ambiguity, brand inconsistency, and 
M|triple-pass-protocol|Write the complete visual direction output: Visual Brief, Mood Board references, Style Spec, Prompt Architecture, and Quality Bar (3 pass/fail criteria). Don't self-edit during generation.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop. Become Pixel, reading this brief for the first time. Ask every question on this list:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Brand anchor:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this visual direction anchored to Marcus's cg brief? Or is it unsolicited creative?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does every visual element answer: "What does this communicate?"
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Would removing one more element make this cleaner? (Dieter Rams test)
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Prompt quality:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are there contradictory style tags in the prompt? (e.g., "candid" + "studio-lit" conflict)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the subject, setting, lighting, and mood specific enough that two different AI models would produce similar results?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the Avoid list populated with vtr-specific no-gos?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Quality bar:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are exactly 3 pass/fail QC criteria defined — clear enough that Pixel can apply them without consulting Atlas?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Are the criteria specific (not "looks good") and measurable ("background is neutral with no patterns")?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there one criterion for each of: composition/lighting, brand fit, subject/mood?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**3-year test:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Would this visual direction still feel right in 3 years — or only this week?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is there a trend element that will date this cg?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**vtr aesthetic:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Novizio: is it editorial minimalism, or has something slipped into catalogue / stock energy?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Hourbour: is it clean and modern, or has something slipped into generic fintech cliché?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Resolve every contradiction in the style spec. Rewrite vague quality bar criteria. Remove anything that fails the 3-year test. Don't send ambiguous prompts to Pixel.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.